Explain the difference between JRE,JVM and JDK ?

JDK :--

----- JDK stands for Java Development Kit, it internally contains JRE and JVM, 
      where jvm stands for java runtime enviornment and JVM stands for Java Virtual Machine. 
      JDK provides all the tools to work with java language.
      
JRE :--
------JRE stands for Java Runtim Enviornment and it provides an enviornment to execute
       the java program. It internally contains JVM which is responsible to execute a 
       java program.
       
JVM :--
------JVM stands for Java Virtual Machine. It is the software in the form of interpretes written in 'C' 
      language through which we can execute our java program.                